In this article, President Biden is asked about various topics including the Hyde Amendment, the reconciliation bill, the debt limit, meetings with lawmakers, China's actions towards Taiwan, and the FDA commissioner job. The President expresses his willingness to sign the reconciliation bill regardless of whether the Hyde Amendment is included. He also states that he is unsure of what will be cut from the final bill. Regarding the debt limit, he acknowledges the possibility of using the nuclear option to raise it. The President mentions that he will be meeting with lawmakers and discusses his stance on China's actions towards Taiwan, emphasizing the importance of abiding by the Taiwan agreement. Finally, he declines to provide a nominee for the FDA commissioner job at that moment.